cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper presents a novel meta-learning algorithm for zero-shot task transfer in computer vision, which involves learning from known tasks to adapt to novel tasks without ground truth. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) and neural networks (cs.NE), which are relevant sub-categories.
